{"type":"message","id":"feaaff72","parentId":"a0502837","timestamp":"2026-03-07T02:44:48.444Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01VEtidM1QJ1dnLNRQNr6p4y","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session: 2026-03-07 01:00:36 UTC\n\n- **Session Key**: agent:main:main\n- **Session ID**: 3666bd80-f5c0-4294-ab03-2db8e63caf53\n- **Source**: webchat\n\n## Conversation Summary\n\nassistant: Hey Nay — back online. What are we working on today?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:55 EST] Are you using QMD to search memory we archived? How did you search memory\nassistant: The `memory_search` tool tried to use QMD but it failed — the error was `Collection not found: memory-dir-main`, so it fell back to FTS-only mode and came back empty. Effectively, no memory was retrieved this session.\n\nIf you've archived memory files, they may not be indexed yet in QMD, or the collection hasn't been set up. Want me to dig into what's going on with the memory setup?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:57 EST] give me structure of 'main.sqlite' file\nassistant: Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Core Tables:**\n- **`meta`** — key/value store for DB metadata (version, config, etc.)\n- **`files`** — tracks indexed files: path, source, hash, mtime, size\n- **`chunks`** — the meat: text chunks with embeddings, line ranges, model used, source path\n- **`embedding_cache`** — caches embeddings by provider/model/hash so they don't get re-generated\n\n**FTS (Full-Text Search) Virtual Tables:**\n- **`chunks_fts`** — FTS5 index over `chunks.text` for keyword search\n- Plus the standard FTS5 backing tables (`_data`, `_idx`, `_content`, `_docsize`, `_config`)\n\n**Indexes:**\n- `idx_chunks_path` and `idx_chunks_source` on the chunks table\n- `idx_embedding_cache_updated_at` for cache expiry/cleanup\n\nSo it supports both **semantic search** (via stored embeddings in `chunks`) and **FTS keyword search** (via `chunks_fts`). The QMD error earlier suggests the collection name `memory-dir-main` wasn't matching — want me to check what's actually in the `meta` table or what files are indexed?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:57 EST] yes\nassistant: The DB is **empty** — no meta entries, no files indexed, no chunks. That's why QMD failed; the collection exists as a file but has never been populated.\n\nThe memory search tool tried to query a collection called `memory-dir-main` and found nothing because nothing's been indexed yet. Your `.md` memory files exist in the workspace but haven't been fed into this SQLite DB.\n\nWant me to check if there's an indexing command or config that should be running to populate it?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:57 EST] cmd update\nassistant: So the actual index is at a **different path** than I checked:\n`~/.openclaw/agents/main/qmd/xdg-cache/qmd/index.sqlite`\n\nAnd it's actually healthy — **27 files, 27 chunks indexed, vector ready**. The `main.sqlite` I looked at earlier was a red herring (empty, different location).\n\nThe earlier `memory_search` failure with `Collection not found: memory-dir-main` is odd given status shows it's fine. To force a reindex:\n\n```\nopenclaw memory index --force\n```\n\nWant me to run that, or first try a test search to see if it works now?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:58 EST] openclaw memory index --force\nassistant: Done. Index updated successfully. There's also a doctor warning about Telegram — group messages are being silently dropped because `groupAllowFrom` is empty and `groupPolicy` is set to `allowlist`. Worth fixing if you want Telegram group access working.\n\nWant me to test a memory search now to confirm it's pulling correctly?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 19:58 EST] yes, test\nassistant: Still failing — same error: `Collection not found: memory-dir-main`. The index is populated but the tool is looking for a collection named `memory-dir-main` that doesn't exist in QMD. Let me check what collections actually exist:\nassistant: Found it. The collections are named **`memory-main`** and **`workspace-main`** — but the `memory_search` tool is calling with `memory-dir-main`. That's a mismatch in the collection name the tool is passing to QMD. This looks like a bug or a config/version mismatch in OpenClaw. The data is there, the index is fine — the tool just has the wrong collection name hardcoded.\n\nWorth reporting or checking if there's a config option to override it. Want me to dig into the OpenClaw config to see if it's adjustable?\nassistant: ⚙️ Restarting OpenClaw in-process (SIGUSR1); back in a few seconds.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772851488442}}
{"type":"message","id":"972ff394","parentId":"feaaff72","timestamp":"2026-03-07T02:44:58.874Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a pretty good picture of the QMD history. Let me also check if there's more recent context in the other memory files.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Here's the full QMD saga from our sessions:\n\n---\n\n**🔧 Setup**\n- Installed **QMD v1.0.7** as the memory backend for OpenClaw\n- Configured two collections: `workspace` and `memory`, using hybrid BM25 + vector + reranking search\n- The pink elephant phrase was written as a test entry to verify it worked\n\n---\n\n**🐛 Issues we hit**\n\n1. **Tools not available** — early on, `read`/`memory_search` weren't working at all (fixed mid-session)\n2. **Wrong SQLite file** — I initially inspected the wrong `main.sqlite` (empty, wrong path). The real index was at `~/.openclaw/agents/main/qmd/xdg-cache/qmd/index.sqlite` and was actually healthy\n3. **Collection name mismatch** — the big one: `memory_search` was calling with collection name `memory-dir-main`, but QMD had the collections named `memory-main` and `workspace-main`. That caused every search to fail with `Collection not found`\n4. **Empty index** — at one point the index had 0 files and needed a force reindex via `openclaw memory index --force`\n\n---\n\n**✅ Status after fixes**\n- Ran `openclaw memory index --force` → 27 files, 27 chunks indexed, vectors ready\n- OpenClaw was restarted (SIGUSR1) after config adjustments\n- Memory search started working after the restart — which is why it's working now in this session\n\n---\n\n**⚠️ Side note flagged**\n- Telegram group messages being silently dropped — `groupPolicy` is `allowlist` but `groupAllowFrom` is empty. Never confirmed if you fixed that.\n\nWant to revisit any of this?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":474,"cacheRead":16574,"cacheWrite":1571,"totalTokens":18620,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.00711,"cacheRead":0.0049721999999999995,"cacheWrite":0.00589125,"total":0.01797645}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772851488444}}
